==================================
MSWL - Developers and Motivations
==================================

Introduction
=============

I going to place the exercises from ``Developers and Motivations`` Subject in Master de Software Libre that I'm coursing in ``Universidad Rey Juan Carlos``.

LaTeX
------

I use LaTeX to develop documents in this repository instead of *restructuredText* that is used in README files.

Summary
========

Brief summary of the exercises.

Developers Characterisation
-----------------------------

This exercise it's about how the world see FLOSS developers and how is reflected in the study from FLOSSProject::

    http://flossproject.org/report/Final4.htm

This exercise is answered in **https://github.com/ricardogarfe/mswl-developer-and-motivations/blob/master/000-developers-characterisation.tex** file.

The Cathedral and the Bazaar
-----------------------------

Revise the content of Eric S. Raymond's essay to answer the following points:

    * In your opinion, which are the 2 most important lessons that we can find in the essay? Provide links and examples to backup your reasoning.
    * Now, find out the 2 most controversial lessons. Again, try to include links and examples to support your comments.

This exercise is answered in **001-the-cathedral-and-the-bazaar.tex** file using references from the article ``The Cathedral and the Bazaar``::

    * http://www.catb.org/esr/writings/homesteading/cathedral-bazaar/index.html

This exercise is answered in **https://github.com/ricardogarfe/mswl-developer-and-motivations/blob/master/002-transactions-on-human-computer-interaction.tex**


Spring Roles Organization
--------------------------

Describe Spring Roles Organization, make a video presentation and a resume:

This exercise is answered in **https://github.com/ricardogarfe/mswl-developer-and-motivations/blob/master/003-spring-roles-organization.tex**

And the video is uploaded here:

http://youtu.be/K_nnmQE9jUA


Final FLOOS Report
-------------------

Written Report about Guido van Rossum creator of Python. Describes his biography and interaction with the community.

This exercise is answered in **https://github.com/ricardogarfe/mswl-developer-and-motivations/blob/master/

